Heat oven to 425 F. Grease baking sheet. Stir together coffee beans, cocoa, salt, chili powder, and brown sugar. Rub chicken pieces with vegetable oil; pat on cocoa mixture. Place coated chicken pieces on prepared baking sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until juices are clear. Meanwhile, prepare SALSA MOLE: Stir together tomatoes, avocado, onion, garlic, cilantro, small chocolate chips and lime juice in medium bowl. Arrange chicken and salsa on large platter. Garnish with cilantro sprigs, if desired.